23.name: Plastic Trays and Tops
23.description:
For deli chicken, single serve meals, prepared foods, baked goods, housewares and hardware, e.g. screws, picture hangers, etc.
• Containers are clear or have black bottom trays with clear domes
• Empty and rinse trays
23.not_include:
White, black or colour foam trays (take to Recycle BC depot), soft plastic packaging for perishable foods, e.g. meat, poultry, fish
or cheese, etc., plastic/foil packaging for items like chewing gum and pills

24.name: Plastic Tubs and Lids
24.description:
For margarine, spreads, yogurt, cottage cheese, sour cream, ice cream, etc.
• Empty and rinse tubs
• Remove lids and place loose in
recycling container
• For single-use coffee and tea
pods: Empty and rinse pods. Remove lids and do not include lids with recycling. Grounds can be composted.
24.not_include: Packaging labelled biodegradable or compostable, plastic or foil lids from coffee and tea pods, coffee grounds (include with green waste, if applicable)

25.name: Plastic Cold Drink Cups with Lids
25.description:
Beverage take out cups
• Empty and rinse cups
• Remove lids and place loose in
recycling container.
25.not_include: Foam cups (take to Recycle BC depot), plastic packaging labelled biodegradable or compostable, napkins (include with green waste, if applicable), straws

26.name: Plastic Garden Pots and Trays
26.description:
For bedding plants, seedlings, vegetable plants, etc.
• Remove remaining soil from garden pots and trays.
26.not_include: Ceramic plant pots, lawn edging, tarps, plastic furniture or toys, garden hoses, plastic string or rope

27.name: Plastic Pails
27.description:
For laundry detergent, ice cream, pet food, etc.
• Recycle BC accepts pails that are less than 25L; larger pails should be disposed of via a commercial hauler.
27.not_include: Plastic paint cans, plastic pails larger than 25L, pails for lubricants and oils

28.name: Microwavable Bowls and Cups
28.description:
For soups and entrees
• Remove lids and place loose in recycling container
28.not_include: Bowls with metal rims, napkins (include with green waste, if applicable), cutlery

29.name: Non-Deposit Glass Bottles and Jars
29.description:
Clear or coloured. Check with your recycling collector for instructions
• Empty and rinse bottles and jars. Labels OK
• Include lids with container recycling
29.not_include: Drinking glasses, dishes, cookware, whole or broken window glass or mirrors, ceramic mugs or other ceramic products, deposit glass bottles (return for deposit refund), light bulbs and light fixtures
